nodes.title: Note 1: Control Panel
widgets_values:
Controlpanel:
Use the Upscale "Yes/No" to apply the whole Upscale process.
Turn it off if you want to prepare your image before upscaling.

To disable the background fix, just set it on "No".

cinematic, volumetric lighting, (masterpiece), top quality, best quality, (photorealistic), hyperrealism, (absurdres), sharp focus, subsurface scattering, intricate details, high quality, ultra high res, 8k, UHD, HDR, DSLR shot, 35mm, (professional photography), RAW,

nodes.title: Note 2: Checkpoint / LoRA
widgets_values:
Choose here your Checkpoint and LoRAs.
But keep the LCM LoRA!
Leave the backgroudn smoother like it is! :D

nodes.title: Note 7: KSampler
widgets_values:
Let denoise on 0.35 and only use the "Control Net - strenght" for "creativity"

I nearly never touch this.
I play only with the control net strenght.

nodes.title: Upscale
widgets_values:
If your image is to big and already sharp enough.
Skip this node with the below "Image Resize by Factor" node.

Just change the input and output to this one!

nodes.title: Note 6: Rescale Factor
widgets_values:
Change here the rescale factor.

I would recommend to upscale iterative.

2x -> 2x -> 2x -> ...

Not 6x instantly as example.

You can also try:
1.5x -> 1.5x -> ...

nodes.title: How big is your upscaled image:
Note 5: Tiled Diffusion
widgets_values:
If you get an error, it could be that your image is to small.
Set Tile_width / Tile_height then to: 512

After that put it back to 1024.

Also to increase speed or lower VRAM usage put tile_overlap to 128 / 256

nodes.title: Note 9: Noise Injection
widgets_values:
Use the Noise Injection for finer.
blend_percentage is to reduce or increase it.
The Preview will show you the "merge".

nodes.title: Note 4: Prompt
widgets_values:
To upscale, just change the prompt to what ever you want.
To avoid eyes, mouthes and noses or stuff like this in bigger images, i would recommend to use only materials like above.

I would recommend to ONLY use detail prompts.

No "Woman, eyes" prompts.

To add more details and contrast use this as negative:

No object, no thing, no material, no still life, human, with human, face, woman face, woman, easynegative, bad-picture-chill-75v,(worst quality, low quality:2.0)

nodes.title: Upscale
widgets_values:
Conncet here the output of:
-CR Upscale Image

or 

-Image Resize by Factor

nodes.title: Upscale
widgets_values:
If you get artefacts trough this, bypass it --------->

In the most cases it helps.

nodes.title: Note 8: IPAdapter
widgets_values:
This is for the multiply face fix.

weight_type (style transfer or composition)

When you see faces or get weird noses / eyes.

Try to set the weight to 2 or higher.

nodes.title: Note 3: ControlNet
widgets_values:
Inpaint as control net + the normal upscaled image as reference.

Lower Strenght = More Creativity 
Higher Strenght = Less Creativity

If you want high changes you can go from 0.00 - 0.1/+++

And to just normal upscale i recommend 0.35 or higher. (Try it out)

nodes.title: IMPORTANT!
widgets_values:
You can only turn 2 on at the same time!

I would recommend to keep inpaint all the timae on.

Switch between Canny and Tile.
